Originating in the ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' sketch [[Wayne's World]], '''schwing''' is a [[slang]] term used as an exclamation of happiness or appreciation for the female form (example: "You've just won the lottery!" "''Schwing!''").

It should not be confused with "schwingen," the German word for "to swing."

Schwing is also an [[Irish language|Irish Gaelic]] colloquialism of appreciation for the male form; it is surprisingly inappropriate to use it about the female form.

This is also the sound a sword makes when it comes out of its metal-lined sheath.

Schwing is also a trademarked brand name of concrete pumps manufactured in Germany and White Bear Lake, MN.
